"It isThe Morning Chronicle of April27, 1890. Just two months ago.""Very good. Now, Mr. Wilson?""Well, it is just as I have beentelling you, Mr. Sherlock Holmes," said Jabez Wilson, mopping his forehead; "Ihave a small pawnbroker's business at Coburg Square, near the City. It's not a very large affair, and of late years it has not done more than just give me a living. I used to be able to keep two assistants, but now I only keep one; and I would have a job to pay him but that he is willingto come for half wages so as tolearn the business."

