"Your French gold?"

"Yes. We had occasion some months ago to strengthenour resources and borrowed forthat purpose 30,000 napoleons from the Bank of France. It has become known thatwe have never had occasion to unpack the money,and that it is still lying in our cellar. The crate upon which Isit contains 2,000 napoleons packed between layers of lead foil. Our reserve ofbullion is muchlarger at present than is usually kept in a single branch office, and the directors have had misgivings upon the subject."

