"IfI tell her shewill not believeme. You may remember the old Persian saying, 'There is danger for him who taketh the tiger cub,and danger alsofor whoso snatches a delusion from a woman.' There is as much sense in Hafiz asin Horace, andas much knowledge of the world."ADVENTURE IV.THE BOSCOMBE VALLEY MYSTERY


Wewere seated atbreakfast one morning, my wife and I, when the maid brought in atelegram. It was from SherlockHolmes and ran in this way:

"Have you a coupleof days to spare? Have just beenwired for fromthe west of England in connection with BoscombeValley tragedy.Shall be glad ifyou will come with me. Air andscenery perfect.Leave Paddington by the 11:15.""What do you say, dear?" saidmy wife, lookingacross at me. "Will you go?"

