" 'That white one with the barred tail, right in themiddle of the flock.'

" 'Oh, very well. Kill it and take it with you.'

"Well,I did what shesaid, Mr. Holmes, and I carriedthe bird all theway to Kilburn.I told my pal what I had done,for he was a manthat it was easy to tell a thing like that to.He laughed untilhe choked, andwe got a knife and opened the goose. My heart turned to water, for there was nosign of the stone, and I knew that some terriblemistake had occurred. I left the bird, rushed back to my sister's, and hurriedinto the back yard. There was not a bird to be seen there.

